			<ns0:name>eaelt...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/103360015124260446450/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">We want our built-in debug stub to support multi-threading targets in all-stop mode.

That means when breakpoint/exception happens, all NaCl app threads should be stopped, so GDB can examine and change their context. When GDB asks to continue, all NaCl app threads should be resumed.

At the moment we only have some implementation for Windows, that uses SuspendThread/ResumeThread.
